  "notes": [
    "QF booking classes have multiple sub-tiers per cabin (e.g. Flexible Business J/C, Business D, Discount Business I). All map to 'business' in this table — actual earning may differ by sub-tier.",
    "Our 'business' category maps to Qantas calculator's 'Discount Business' tier. The calculator also shows a higher 'Business' tier (~5 more SCs) which we do not model separately.",
    "Our 'flexible_economy' maps to the Qantas calculator's 'Flexible Economy' tier, which earns at 50% of the Discount Business rate for all verified routes.",
    "Our 'premium_economy' maps to the Qantas calculator's 'Premium Economy' tier (not 'Discount Premium Economy').",
    "QF does not fly SYD→DOH. Doha is Qatar Airways territory; the aus_east_coast_middle_east table applies only to Dubai (DXB) and other Middle East destinations actually served by QF.",
    "QF does not fly non-stop Australia→East Coast USA as of 2026. Project Sunrise (SYD→LHR/JFK non-stop) is planned but not yet in service.",
    "Domestic Australian destinations (ADL, CNS, DRW) do not have explicit route tables — they fall to distance_tables. Perth (PER) earns at a specific lower rate and has an explicit table."
